Bug report: Background image not updating.


Environment:

Platform- Trello
Browser- Brave
OS- Windows 11
URL- https://trello.com
Account Type- Standard user
Network- Stable (500 Mbps)


Title: Board background image fails to update after selecting a new background.


Severity: Medium

Priority: Medium


Preconditions:
- User is logged in
- At least one board exists
- Board has a default background assigned


Steps to Reproduce:
- Open Trello and navigate to any existing board
- Click Show Menu on the right sidebar
- Select Background
- Choose any new background image from the gallery
- Wait for the change to apply


Expected Result: The selected background image is immediately applied to the board and displayed to the user without delay.


Actual Result: The board background does not update, and the previous background remains visible.
Refreshing the page eventually applies the new background.


Reproducibility: Inconsistent (~40% of the times tested).


Additional Notes:
- Happens intermittently; issue reproduced 4 out of 10 times
- No console errors detected
- Possibly related to caching or asynchronous UI updates


(Disclaimer: This is a fictitious report meant as a knowledge showcase, none of the issues displayed above are present in the website in question.)
